The paper focuses on ranking the future popularity of new publications and young researchers in the field of scientific literature, which involves analyzing text features and constructing time-aware weighted graphs. This aligns with several sub-categories of arXiv CS, including Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Digital Libraries (cs.DL), Sociology (cs.SOC), and Databases (cs.DB). However, given the emphasis on text analysis and ranking, cs.IR and cs.SI are the most likely sub-categories.
